headline: Assessing Mondelez (MDLZ) Valuation After Recent Share Price Weakness and Ongoing Earnings Growth
summary: Mondelez International (MDLZ) has quietly drifted lower this past quarter, with the stock down about 12% over the past 3 months despite steady single digit revenue and double digit earnings growth. See our latest analysis for Mondelez International. Zooming out, Mondelez’s 1 year total shareholder return of around negative 8 percent and 3 year total shareholder return of roughly negative 12 percent show that momentum has clearly faded even as earnings keep grinding higher.
